{
  "text": "Moreover, NLC I showed in absolute the best performance, giving rise to a complete drug release within 6 h, never achieved with the previous SLN formulations Figure 3 . Diuretic effect expressed in terms of: volume of excreted urine (mL) (A); diuretic activity (ml/100g body weight) (B) and diuretic index (C) after oral administration (drug dose of 10 mg kg \u00c01 ) of the selected HCT-loaded NLC I , NLC II and NLC 1C formulations. [CITATION_1] . Such a finding confirmed the microemulsion technique as the most effective method to produce HCT-loaded NLC formulations.",
